parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can prevent the seat belt from latching or releasing, which can lead to accidents or injuries in the event of sudden stops or crashes.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle will not latch
the seat belt buckle will not stay closed
the red release button is broken
the seat belt is stuck and cannot be released
the seat belt is jammed or stuck in the retracted position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to accidents or injuries in the event of sudden stops or crashes.
symptoms: the seat belt does not retract
the seat belt is stuck or jammed in the retracted position
the seat belt is loose and does not provide proper restraint.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Missing Seat Belt Recall
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or failure to receive a recalled seat belt part can leave the vehicle occupant at risk of injury or accident due to a faulty seat belt.
symptoms: The consumer is waiting for a seat belt buckle or retractor replacement
the dealer or manufacturer claims there is no recall
the consumer is unaware of a recall or has not received the necessary replacement parts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the fuel gauge can cause the driver to be unaware of the fuel level, leading to potential engine stalling, fuel starvation, and safety risks.
symptoms: The fuel gauge does not register fuel levels
the fuel gauge needle does not move

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel leaks from the tank can cause fires, explosions, and environmental hazards, while separation of the tank from its mounting can lead to accidents.
symptoms: the fuel tank has pulled away from its mounting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Leaks in the fuel injection system can cause fuel to leak onto hot engine components, leading to fires and safety risks.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the fuel injection system
fuel smell in the engine compartment

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system fires can cause damage to the vehicle, injuries, and fatalities.
Tire blowouts or failures can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities, especially when traveling at high speeds.
Tire tread separation can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities, especially when traveling at high speeds.
Defective tire design or manufacturing can lead to tire failures, blowouts, or tread separation, causing loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
